Center Wu Zongxin, founder&gt;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Workplace Tips &#8211; 30 Thoughts of the General Manager of &#8220;Understanding&#8221; &lt;Taiwan&#8217;s Ogilvy &amp; Mather Group Managing Director Xie Xinhui&gt;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Igniting the soul of the supervisor &lt;the general manager of Yunlang Tourism Group Sheng Zhiren&gt;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Innovation and Entrepreneurial Thinking Seminar &lt;General Manager of XRSPACE Tao Yunzhi&gt;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Timing, Opportunity: Business Changes and Challenges in the Next Decade &lt;The Electronic Times \u300aDIGITIMES\u300b,Huang Qinyong, Founder\/President&gt;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Coexistence with AI: Today I have an appointment with the political commissar Tang Feng, the political commissar of the &lt;Executive Yuan&gt;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Introduction to 3D Integrated Circuits and Heterogeneous Integration and My &lt;\u967d\u660e\u4ea4\u901a\u5927\u5b78\u9673\u51a0\u80fd\u6559\u6388&gt;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Journey of Learning The World of Giant &#8211; Key Decisions &lt;Luo Xiang&#8217;an, founder of the Giant Group and former CEO of the giant group&gt;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https:\/\/www.playnitride.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/ESG-2-5-1-2-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1157\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.playnitride.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/ESG-2-5-1-2-scaled.jpg 2560w, https:\/\/www.playnitride.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/ESG-2-5-1-2-768x576.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.playnitride.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/ESG-2-5-1-2-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/www.playnitride.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/ESG-2-5-1-2-2048x1536.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Corporate&nbsp;Governance<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Board Members<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1760\" height=\"1616\" src=\"https:\/\/www.playnitride.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/\u8463\u4e8b\u6703\u82f1\u6587.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1784\"\/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>The Audit Committee<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Audit Committee of the Company aims to assist the Board in performing its oversight of the quality and integrity of the Company in the implementation of relevant accounting, auditing, financial reporting processes and financial controls.&nbsp;&nbsp;Matters reviewed by the Audit Committee include financial reporting, the effectiveness of the internal control system, the appointment, dismissal or remuneration of certified accountants and the assessment of their independence, and the appointment and removal of the head of finance, accounting or internal audit.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>The Remuneration Committee<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Company&#8217;s Remuneration Committee aims to assist the Board in implementing and evaluating the Company&#8217;s overall remuneration and benefits policies, systems and structures, as well as the remuneration of Directors and Managers, and to make recommendations to the Board for its decision-making.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Corporate Governance Operations<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Communication with independent directors&nbsp;                                                                                          Directors&#8217; further education <\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Sustainable Development Committee<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>In order to strengthen corporate governance, practice corporate social responsibility, and implement sustainable business to keep pace with international trends, the Company resolved at the 12th meeting of the 3rd Board of Directors on 9 September 2021 to establish a &#8220;Sustainable Development Committee&#8221; under the Office of the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Sustainability Report&nbsp;<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Our 2021 Sustainability Report&nbsp;has been prepared on the basis of the Sustainability Accounting Standard in terms of the identification of stakeholders and the impact assessment of sustainability issues.&nbsp; In 2023, we follow the GRI Sustainability Reporting Standards (GRI Standards), Sustainability Accounting Standards Board (SASB) and Climate-related Financial Disclosure (TCFD) disclosure standards to gradually better disclosures in sustainable reporting.&nbsp;&nbsp;In accordance with the above standards, we issued our 2022 sustainability report.                                                                                                                                      Click here for our reports\uff1a<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.playnitride.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/PlayNitride-2021-SASB-Report-EN.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">2021 Sustainability Report<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.playnitride.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/PlayNitride-2022SustainabilityReport-EN.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">2022 Sustainability Report<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Internal Audit<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">1. <strong>Purpose of Internal Audit\u00a0<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>The design, implementation and internal inspection of the Company&#8217;s internal control system shall be handled in accordance with the guidelines for the establishment of the internal control system and related laws and regulations of the public offering company.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>2. Internal Audit Organization<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>The Company has set up an internal audit unit, which is subordinate to the Board of Directors to work exclusively for internal audit work.&nbsp;&nbsp;In accordance with the company&#8217;s operating scale, business situation, management needs and other relevant laws and regulations, the Audit Supervisor shall be assigned full time with a suitable and appropriate number of people to which he belongs.&nbsp;&nbsp;The appointment and removal of the Head of Internal Audit shall be subject to the consent of the Audit Committee and a resolution of the Board of Directors.&nbsp;&nbsp;The qualifications of internal auditors meet the statutory requirements for appointment and continue to study for the required number of hours.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">3. <strong>Operation of Internal Audit<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>The internal auditors perform their duties in a spirit of transcendent independence and with an objective and impartial standpoint, with due professional attention.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Audit Supervisor regularly reports to the Audit Committee on audit operations and attends the Board of Directors as an observer.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company&#8217;s internal audit business is based on the results of the risk assessment to prepare an annual audit plan, specifying the audit items, time, procedures and methods.&nbsp;&nbsp;Auditors conduct regular or irregular routine and project audits, and audit results are submitted to the Audit Committee with working papers and related materials to ensure that the Company&#8217;s internal control system is continuously and effectively implemented.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>All units and subsidiaries within the Company are urged to regularly assess the effectiveness of the internal control system on a regular basis every year.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The internal control self-assessment should be performed by the head of each unit according to the actual operation content of the department, the internal control system design and implementation effectiveness assessment.&nbsp;&nbsp;And then the internal audit unit reviews the self-assessment report of each unit and its subsidiaries, and the internal control deficiencies and abnormal matters found by the audit unit, as the main basis for the board of directors and the general manager to evaluate the effectiveness of the overall internal control system and issue an internal control system statement.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Internal auditors shall disclose the deficiencies and abnormalities in the internal control system discovered in the internal audit operations, listed in the internal control system declaration, and self-assessment and certified accountant project review, and follow up after the report is audited, and make a tracking report on a quarterly basis to determine that the relevant units have taken appropriate improvement measures in a timely manner and listed as an important item in the performance appraisal of various departments.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;After the audit report and the tracking report are audited, they shall be submitted to the Audit Committee for review before the end of the month following the completion of the audit project.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If the internal auditor discovers a major violation or the company is in danger of being seriously damaged, it shall immediately make a report and notify the board of directors and the Audit Committee.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Important Corporate Rules<\/strong>&nbsp;(Please click on the project link)&nbsp;<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.playnitride.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/PN_\u516c\u53f8\u7ae0\u7a0b-20220214-V11.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Articles of Incorporation<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.playnitride.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/PN_CA120-02-V1.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Rules of Procedure of the Shareholders Meeting<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.playnitride.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/PN_CA121-03-V1.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"